WEBVTT

00:01.909 --> 00:04.169
<i>- The most secure prison
in all of Europe.</i>

00:04.328 --> 00:07.164
<i>- There were barbed wires.
There were concrete walls.</i>

00:07.248 --> 00:08.582
There were checkpoints.

00:08.666 --> 00:11.010
<i>It was a multilayered security.</i>

00:11.094 --> 00:13.512
<i>- A tight-knit group
of hardened inmates...</i>

00:13.596 --> 00:15.756
- I had to stay in the jail
for the rest of my life.

00:15.849 --> 00:17.507
- People want to escape.

00:17.600 --> 00:20.019
<i>- Embroiled
in a bloody conflict...</i>

00:20.103 --> 00:22.179
<i>- Prisoners would be beaten
on a daily basis.</i>

00:22.263 --> 00:24.014
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:24.098 --> 00:27.192
- In 1983, we had
22 prison staff murdered.

00:28.686 --> 00:31.697
<i>- Plan an escape
of epic proportions...</i>

00:31.856 --> 00:34.024
- The more people
that you're trying to get out,

00:34.108 --> 00:36.952
<i>it's a bigger operation,
more things can go wrong.</i>

00:37.037 --> 00:38.945
<i>- Hoping to pull off
one of the largest</i>

00:39.030 --> 00:41.364
<i>and most elaborate
prison escapes...</i>

00:41.449 --> 00:43.208
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:43.367 --> 00:45.210
<i>In all of history.</i>

00:45.369 --> 00:50.549
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:50.708 --> 00:54.887
Some of the greatest stories
ever told start behind bars.

00:55.046 --> 00:56.889
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:57.048 --> 00:59.049
<i>Locked up in the most
notorious prisons</i>

00:59.133 --> 01:00.726
<i>in the world.</i>

01:00.885 --> 01:05.230
<i>Spied on by guards
and fellow prisoners.</i>

01:05.389 --> 01:08.892
<i>It takes a devious mind
to find a way out.</i>

01:08.976 --> 01:10.644
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:10.737 --> 01:13.563
<i>It could lead you to freedom</i>

01:13.656 --> 01:15.240
<i>or it could cost you your life.</i>

01:15.399 --> 01:17.576
<i>[gunshot]</i>

01:17.660 --> 01:19.995
<i>But wouldn't you try...</i>
[all shouting]

01:20.154 --> 01:21.580
When you have
nothing left to lose?

01:21.739 --> 01:28.545
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:33.593 --> 01:35.502
This is a typical cell

01:35.595 --> 01:39.339
in one of the most notorious
prisons ever built in Europe.

01:39.432 --> 01:42.092
The accommodations are sparse:

01:42.176 --> 01:45.679
bed, the chair,

01:45.772 --> 01:49.516
and this pot here?

01:49.609 --> 01:51.944
That's the toilet.

01:52.028 --> 01:55.605
<i>This is not
some Victorian dungeon.</i>

01:55.690 --> 01:59.618
<i>This is 1980s Northern Ireland.</i>

01:59.702 --> 02:03.363
<i>It's a prison built next
to a British military base.</i>

02:03.447 --> 02:08.127
Its name: the Maze.

02:08.286 --> 02:10.287
Over the years,
the legend of this prison's

02:10.380 --> 02:14.133
impenetrable security has grown.

02:14.292 --> 02:17.636
No one can get out
of this godforsaken place.

02:17.795 --> 02:22.299
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:22.383 --> 02:24.143
<i>But in the early 1980s,</i>

02:24.302 --> 02:27.437
<i>a group of inmates decide
to attempt the impossible.</i>

02:29.065 --> 02:32.976
- What makes the Maze escape
in 1983 so controversial

02:33.060 --> 02:34.895
is the fact that it was

02:34.979 --> 02:38.815
<i>the largest escape
in British penal history.</i>

02:38.900 --> 02:42.661
<i>It was also composed
of prisoners who were deemed</i>

02:42.820 --> 02:45.739
<i>some of the most dangerous
in British prison.</i>

02:46.833 --> 02:48.825
<i>And finally,
it was done from a prison</i>

02:48.918 --> 02:53.246
that was deemed the most
secure complex in Europe.

02:53.331 --> 02:56.592
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:56.751 --> 02:58.752
<i>- The Maze is not just secure.</i>

02:58.845 --> 03:00.086
<i>It's a hellhole.</i>

03:00.180 --> 03:03.849
<i>Guards control the prisoners
with an iron fist.</i>

03:04.008 --> 03:07.269
<i>- The situation between
the guards and the prisoners</i>

03:07.428 --> 03:09.346
was one of enemy combatants.

03:09.430 --> 03:11.014
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:11.107 --> 03:13.266
<i>Guards were beating
prisoners daily.</i>

03:13.351 --> 03:14.601
<i>And then on the outside,</i>

03:14.685 --> 03:16.028
<i>prisoners went out of their way</i>

03:16.187 --> 03:19.689
<i>to kill prison guards
when they get out of the Maze.</i>

03:19.774 --> 03:21.450
<i>- This is because
the Maze prisoners</i>

03:21.609 --> 03:23.702
<i>aren't ordinary prisoners.</i>

03:23.786 --> 03:26.947
<i>Most are here for taking part
in a bloody conflict</i>

03:27.031 --> 03:29.374
<i>known as the Troubles.</i>

03:29.533 --> 03:31.543
[explosion]

03:31.702 --> 03:33.962
[whistling]

03:34.121 --> 03:35.631
<i>- Troubles is what the Irish,</i>

03:35.790 --> 03:37.207
in their penchant
for understatement,

03:37.300 --> 03:39.551
called their unsettled
uncivil war.

03:41.054 --> 03:43.555
<i>It's about the status
of Northern Ireland.</i>

03:43.714 --> 03:45.131
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:45.216 --> 03:46.716
<i>- At the Maze,
many of the prisoners</i>

03:46.809 --> 03:49.061
<i>belong to the Irish
Republican Army</i>

03:49.220 --> 03:51.188
<i>or IRA for short.</i>

03:52.807 --> 03:55.892
<i>They are Catholics fighting
to reunite Northern Ireland</i>

03:55.977 --> 03:59.145
<i>with Ireland.</i>

03:59.230 --> 04:02.399
<i>The guards, on the other hand,
are largely Protestant,</i>

04:02.483 --> 04:06.736
<i>who want the country to remain
a part of the United Kingdom.</i>

04:06.821 --> 04:09.406
<i>Inside the walls of the Maze,</i>

04:09.490 --> 04:13.252
<i>these opposing sides are
forced into close contact.</i>

04:14.495 --> 04:18.248
<i>The atmosphere
is highly charged,</i>

04:18.332 --> 04:21.093
<i>which demands intense security.</i>

04:21.252 --> 04:24.587
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:24.681 --> 04:26.506
<i>- I've been
in high-security prisons</i>

04:26.599 --> 04:27.924
<i>throughout the United States</i>

04:28.017 --> 04:30.010
<i>and in various parts of Europe.</i>

04:30.103 --> 04:32.679
And walking in there felt like
the most secure prison

04:32.772 --> 04:34.347
I had personally ever been in.

04:34.432 --> 04:36.433
<i>There were barbed wires.</i>

04:36.517 --> 04:39.769
<i>There were concrete walls.
There were checkpoints.</i>

04:39.862 --> 04:42.605
<i>It was a multilayered security.</i>

04:42.699 --> 04:45.784
- No combination of tunneling,
cunning disguises,

04:45.943 --> 04:47.869
or brute force
is going to solve the riddle

04:48.029 --> 04:51.031
of getting out of this lockbox.

04:51.124 --> 04:53.875
But of the 833 prisoners here

04:53.960 --> 04:56.953
in 1983,

04:57.046 --> 04:59.631
there are some
who are willing to try.

04:59.790 --> 05:04.794
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:04.879 --> 05:08.131
<i>- I was doing two lives
and 25 years.</i>

05:08.215 --> 05:09.799
<i>That meant
I would stay in the jail</i>

05:09.884 --> 05:10.884
<i>for the rest of my life.</i>

05:10.977 --> 05:11.893
<i>If I didn't escape,</i>

05:12.053 --> 05:14.646
that was my life
from that point on.

05:14.805 --> 05:18.558
- Gerry Kelly was convicted
in 1973 for his involvement

05:18.642 --> 05:22.487
<i>in the Old Bailey bombs
at the Law Courts in London,</i>

05:22.646 --> 05:24.823
<i>in which 200 people were injured</i>

05:24.907 --> 05:27.075
<i>and one person died
of a heart attack at it.</i>

05:28.828 --> 05:32.664
<i>- Gerry Kelly isn't alone
in his desire to escape.</i>

05:32.749 --> 05:36.910
<i>Another IRA member
is also desperate to get out.</i>

05:36.994 --> 05:39.504
<i>Brendan "Bik" McFarlane.</i>

05:39.663 --> 05:45.668
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:45.762 --> 05:47.512
<i>Bik McFarlane is in the Maze</i>

05:47.597 --> 05:49.181
<i>serving a life sentence
for his part</i>

05:49.340 --> 05:52.851
<i>in an attack and bombing
of a bar,</i>

05:53.010 --> 05:56.346
<i>which killed 5
and injured more than 60.</i>

05:56.430 --> 05:58.348
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:58.432 --> 06:00.525
<i>- Bik and Gerry had
both tried to escape</i>

06:00.610 --> 06:03.520
<i>and had escaped from
various jails and prisons.</i>

06:03.604 --> 06:05.105
<i>And Gerry escaped from a prison</i>

06:05.189 --> 06:06.531
<i>when he was just a kid.</i>

06:06.690 --> 06:08.858
And Bik had tried to escape
from the Maze

06:08.943 --> 06:11.444
dressed as a priest,
but they caught him.

06:11.537 --> 06:16.282
- Trying to focus on escaping,
wasn't just me personally.

06:16.367 --> 06:19.285
<i>People want to escape.</i>

06:19.379 --> 06:22.047
<i>- Gerry and Bik began working
with a larger group</i>

06:22.206 --> 06:26.626
<i>of IRA inmates
on an escape plan.</i>

06:26.710 --> 06:30.046
- The escape plan started

06:30.131 --> 06:33.141
<i>after the IRA camp in the prison</i>

06:33.300 --> 06:34.893
<i>noticed that so many prisoners</i>

06:35.052 --> 06:38.805
<i>were trying to come up
with escape ideas.</i>

06:38.889 --> 06:42.734
<i>They pulled together a team
to form an escape committee.</i>

06:42.893 --> 06:44.319
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:44.478 --> 06:46.229
<i>- The IRA escape committee</i>

06:46.322 --> 06:49.324
<i>wants to do
something unimaginable:</i>

06:49.483 --> 06:52.577
<i>break out not just
one or two men,</i>

06:52.662 --> 06:54.237
<i>but dozens,</i>

06:54.321 --> 06:57.490
<i>an escape so big
and unprecedented</i>

06:57.575 --> 07:01.086
<i>that it will embarrass
the British government</i>

07:01.245 --> 07:05.382
<i>and its Prime Minister,
Margaret Thatcher.</i>

07:06.750 --> 07:08.918
<i>That is, if it succeeds.</i>

07:09.003 --> 07:11.588
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:11.681 --> 07:14.757
- The more people
that you try to get out,

07:14.842 --> 07:17.436
<i>it's a bigger operation,
more things can go wrong.</i>

07:17.595 --> 07:22.599
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:22.692 --> 07:25.852
<i>- The Maze is just that:
a maze.</i>

07:25.945 --> 07:29.197
<i>And it will not give up
its security sequence easily.</i>

07:29.356 --> 07:31.691
<i>- We had to demystify the jail.</i>

07:31.775 --> 07:34.119
It's a huge jail.
It's 360 acres.

07:34.278 --> 07:38.281
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:38.374 --> 07:41.034
<i>- The IRA prisoners
pass information</i>

07:41.118 --> 07:44.129
<i>about the layout
of this huge, sprawling prison</i>

07:44.288 --> 07:47.549
<i>using an ingenious
communication system.</i>

07:47.633 --> 07:51.127
<i>- They were basically written
on cigarette papers,</i>

07:51.212 --> 07:54.973
which were very fine
and very small writing.

07:55.057 --> 07:58.310
Usually had to prep it
so that it could be read.

07:58.394 --> 08:00.395
<i>- And you covered it
with stretch and seal.</i>

08:00.480 --> 08:03.139
Stretch and seal is that
for wrapping up sandwiches,

08:03.224 --> 08:05.400
<i>which is airtight
once you wrap it.</i>

08:05.559 --> 08:08.570
<i>- These prisoners passed notes
to one another during meals</i>

08:08.654 --> 08:10.396
<i>and at Sunday Mass.</i>

08:10.481 --> 08:13.241
<i>And hidden inside a cheek,</i>

08:13.326 --> 08:15.410
<i>these communications
can even be passed</i>

08:15.569 --> 08:18.330
<i>to and from outside visitors.</i>

08:18.414 --> 08:20.081
- That was a great excuse
to kiss someone.

08:20.166 --> 08:22.075
[laughs]

08:22.168 --> 08:24.002
<i>- These illicit comms begin</i>

08:24.161 --> 08:26.254
<i>to paint a picture
of the Maze's layout.</i>

08:27.590 --> 08:31.343
<i>It's not one prison.
It's several.</i>

08:31.502 --> 08:34.179
<i>There are eight
self-contained prison blocks</i>

08:34.338 --> 08:36.181
<i>known as H-Blocks.</i>

08:36.340 --> 08:39.259
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:39.343 --> 08:42.270
<i>- The H-Blocks were
in the shape of an H</i>

08:42.429 --> 08:44.606
<i>if you view them from the air.</i>

08:44.690 --> 08:46.599
<i>- Each one of these H-Blocks</i>

08:46.692 --> 08:50.520
<i>has its own security system
of fences and checkpoints</i>

08:50.604 --> 08:53.698
<i>that lead to the prison's
main gate.</i>

08:53.783 --> 08:57.869
<i>The escapees desperately need
a map of these checkpoints.</i>

08:58.028 --> 09:02.865
<i>But their tiny comms can't
convey diagrams or pictures.</i>

09:02.959 --> 09:07.537
<i>That's where
the IRA's large network</i>

09:07.621 --> 09:08.880
<i>comes into play.</i>

09:09.039 --> 09:11.040
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:11.125 --> 09:13.552
<i>- To get around that,
the IRA was able</i>

09:13.636 --> 09:16.546
<i>to get aerial photos
of the prison</i>

09:16.630 --> 09:18.974
<i>in one
of the British newspapers.</i>

09:19.133 --> 09:22.468
<i>And so that's how the IRA
got around the whole idea</i>

09:22.562 --> 09:24.804
of knowing the layout.

09:24.888 --> 09:27.566
<i>- Once that photo
gets smuggled in,</i>

09:27.725 --> 09:31.069
<i>the Maze's secrets
are laid bare.</i>

09:31.228 --> 09:33.896
<i>- We were able to build up
a complete profile</i>

09:33.981 --> 09:36.157
<i>of the entire prison.</i>

09:36.317 --> 09:39.411
And I was able to draw maps.

09:39.570 --> 09:41.571
<i>- With the layout
of the prison in hand,</i>

09:41.655 --> 09:43.740
<i>the next challenge is
how to make this</i>

09:43.824 --> 09:45.908
<i>a mass escape.</i>

09:45.993 --> 09:47.669
<i>Scaling the walls would be sure</i>

09:47.828 --> 09:50.338
<i>to attract attention quickly.</i>

09:50.497 --> 09:52.507
<i>Digging a tunnel is better</i>

09:52.592 --> 09:55.918
<i>for getting many prisoners
out at once.</i>

09:56.003 --> 09:58.013
<i>But the size
of the prison complex means</i>

09:58.097 --> 10:01.090
<i>digging it could take years.</i>

10:01.175 --> 10:03.852
<i>Only one plan seems feasible:</i>

10:04.011 --> 10:06.521
<i>commandeering a delivery truck</i>

10:06.680 --> 10:08.848
<i>and filling it with prisoners.</i>

10:08.932 --> 10:11.351
<i>But in order to hijack a truck,</i>

10:11.435 --> 10:14.237
<i>you first have to have control
of an H-Block.</i>

10:15.939 --> 10:19.451
- And I came up with this idea
of taking over a H-Block.

10:19.610 --> 10:23.529
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:23.623 --> 10:26.875
<i>- The escape committee decides
to target H-Block 7</i>

10:27.034 --> 10:32.038
<i>because all the prisoners
within that block are IRA.</i>

10:32.131 --> 10:34.624
<i>There will be no chance
that prisoners not escaping</i>

10:34.708 --> 10:36.468
<i>would rat out the plan.</i>

10:36.627 --> 10:39.387
<i>The IRA maintains strict control</i>

10:39.472 --> 10:41.464
<i>of all its members.</i>

10:41.557 --> 10:43.308
<i>The committee elects
as its leader</i>

10:43.467 --> 10:47.136
<i>famed IRA veteran Bobby Storey.</i>

10:47.221 --> 10:52.725
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:52.818 --> 10:54.653
<i>- Bobby was kind of a legend</i>

10:54.812 --> 10:58.323
because he was such
a highly active operator.

10:58.407 --> 11:01.493
<i>He finally got jammed up
on a gun possession charge.</i>

11:01.652 --> 11:03.995
<i>And that's what he landed
in the Maze for.</i>

11:04.154 --> 11:07.832
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:07.991 --> 11:10.743
- Bobby Storey was capable
of reading situations

11:10.836 --> 11:12.495
<i>very, very quickly,</i>

11:12.588 --> 11:14.839
<i>very astutely,
and very clinically</i>

11:14.998 --> 11:19.177
and was one who inspired people
in getting things done.

11:19.336 --> 11:21.587
<i>- With Bobby's guidance,
the men quickly decide</i>

11:21.672 --> 11:23.848
<i>that the only way
to pull off a mass escape</i>

11:24.007 --> 11:28.428
<i>is by taking over
H-Block 7's restricted area,</i>

11:28.512 --> 11:31.523
<i>the crossbar of the H.</i>

11:31.682 --> 11:34.183
- The guards would have been
in that sort of middle area.

11:34.268 --> 11:35.685
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:35.769 --> 11:40.031
<i>- The crossbar also contains
the H-Block's only exit.</i>

11:40.116 --> 11:42.826
<i>And it's where
the delivery trucks arrive.</i>

11:44.453 --> 11:48.948
<i>Their escape hinges on somehow
getting access to this area.</i>

11:49.041 --> 11:51.701
<i>They have an ingenious idea.</i>

11:51.794 --> 11:54.629
<i>And it involves a mop
and a broom.</i>

11:58.801 --> 12:01.720
- Jobs were crucial
to the escape.

12:01.879 --> 12:04.389
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:04.473 --> 12:08.643
<i>- An orderly's job
in any prison is maintenance.</i>

12:08.802 --> 12:11.813
<i>You clean, you brush, you mop.</i>

12:11.972 --> 12:13.890
Generally things like that.

12:13.974 --> 12:16.225
<i>- The escape crew
slowly infiltrates</i>

12:16.318 --> 12:19.896
<i>H-7's secure areas as cleaners.</i>

12:19.980 --> 12:22.064
<i>And the guards get used to them.</i>

12:22.149 --> 12:28.321
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:28.414 --> 12:30.665
<i>All is on track</i>

12:30.824 --> 12:32.575
<i>until a guard from another block</i>

12:32.659 --> 12:35.003
<i>recognizes Bik McFarlane</i>

12:35.087 --> 12:38.089
<i>in this secure area.</i>

12:38.248 --> 12:40.082
<i>- He knew me by first-name terms</i>

12:40.176 --> 12:42.677
<i>and engaged
in conversation with me.</i>

12:42.762 --> 12:44.420
<i>Said, "What are you doing?"</i>

12:44.505 --> 12:46.672
I said, "I'm just tidying up
a few things out here."

12:46.766 --> 12:49.759
<i>He immediately went down
to the senior officers' room.</i>

12:49.843 --> 12:51.260
<i>And he said to the two of them,</i>

12:51.345 --> 12:53.429
<i>"What is he doing
out of his cell?"</i>

12:53.514 --> 12:55.431
<i>And they said, "Well, he's one
of the orderlies."</i>

12:55.524 --> 12:57.934
"Doing what?"
"Cleaning up here."

12:58.018 --> 13:00.528
<i>And he told 'em,
"You will rue the day.</i>

13:00.613 --> 13:05.024
"I wouldn't let him or Storey
or Kelly out of their wing.

13:05.117 --> 13:07.118
<i>"Let them sit in their cell.</i>

13:07.277 --> 13:09.278
"You should not allow
people like that

13:09.371 --> 13:12.281
out into sensitive areas."

13:12.366 --> 13:14.959
- These guys were the hardest
of the IRA men in there.

13:15.118 --> 13:16.536
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:16.629 --> 13:20.289
<i>For this guard to see
these guys all of a sudden,</i>

13:20.374 --> 13:22.050
<i>"Oh, yeah, we'll go along
with the prison regime,"</i>

13:22.134 --> 13:23.384
<i>that didn't add up.</i>

13:23.544 --> 13:25.628
It smelled.
And he was right.

13:25.712 --> 13:26.805
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:26.964 --> 13:29.140
<i>- If the prison's
administration decides</i>

13:29.299 --> 13:32.051
<i>that Bik or his coconspirators
can't work</i>

13:32.135 --> 13:34.312
<i>in this restricted area,</i>

13:34.471 --> 13:36.397
<i>they'll never get out
of their H-Block,</i>

13:36.557 --> 13:38.307
<i>let alone drive
out of the prison</i>

13:38.392 --> 13:41.060
<i>in the back of a delivery truck.</i>

13:41.153 --> 13:44.146
<i>They will be trapped
in the Maze for years.</i>

13:44.231 --> 13:48.576
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:54.074 --> 13:58.828
<i>- A group of IRA members
in Her Majesty's Prison Maze</i>

13:58.921 --> 14:02.582
is planning an escape,
an audacious one.

14:02.666 --> 14:05.009
It involves dozens of men

14:05.168 --> 14:08.096
and getting access to this
off-limits control room.

14:08.255 --> 14:09.505
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

14:09.598 --> 14:13.434
The plan is working
until one man, Bik McFarlane,

14:13.519 --> 14:16.354
is flagged as a security risk.

14:16.513 --> 14:18.356
Now the whole escape
is in jeopardy.

14:20.025 --> 14:23.686
- There was an argument ensued
because he had said,

14:23.779 --> 14:26.447
"If I were the governor
in this block,

14:26.532 --> 14:28.107
they wouldn't be
out of their cells."

14:28.191 --> 14:29.450
<i>To which he was told,</i>

14:29.535 --> 14:31.870
<i>"Well, you're not
the governor in this block.</i>

14:32.029 --> 14:34.113
<i>And this is the way
we run it."</i>

14:34.197 --> 14:36.040
So he says,
"Well, you're making a mistake

14:36.125 --> 14:37.700
and you will rue the day."

14:37.793 --> 14:40.453
And I didn't see him after that.

14:40.537 --> 14:41.713
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:41.797 --> 14:45.049
<i>- The IRA conspirators
can keep their jobs</i>

14:45.208 --> 14:47.877
<i>in the restricted crossbar
of their H-Block.</i>

14:47.970 --> 14:49.879
<i>And they can focus on accessing</i>

14:49.963 --> 14:52.307
<i>its most secure area,</i>

14:52.466 --> 14:54.717
<i>the control room.</i>

14:54.801 --> 14:56.719
<i>This is the main point
of communication</i>

14:56.803 --> 14:59.722
<i>between the outside world
and the block.</i>

14:59.806 --> 15:04.235
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:04.394 --> 15:06.321
- You don't control that,
you're not getting to step two,

15:06.405 --> 15:07.980
step three, step four.

15:08.073 --> 15:09.649
You had to get in there.

15:09.733 --> 15:12.401
<i>You had to be able to disarm
the person</i>

15:12.486 --> 15:15.246
who would raise the alarm
during an escape.

15:15.405 --> 15:18.333
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:18.492 --> 15:21.836
<i>- Prisoners may be allowed in
the restricted areas to clean,</i>

15:21.995 --> 15:23.588
<i>but under no circumstances</i>

15:23.672 --> 15:26.591
<i>are they allowed
in the control room.</i>

15:26.750 --> 15:30.670
<i>Its door must remain
locked at all times.</i>

15:30.754 --> 15:32.088
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:32.172 --> 15:33.932
<i>The conspirators realize</i>

15:34.091 --> 15:36.267
<i>their only chance of getting in</i>

15:36.352 --> 15:40.012
<i>is to cultivate friendships
with the guards.</i>

15:40.097 --> 15:42.264
<i>That's an almost impossible task</i>

15:42.349 --> 15:44.016
<i>considering the current
political climate</i>

15:44.109 --> 15:45.685
<i>in Northern Ireland</i>

15:45.769 --> 15:47.937
<i>and especially within the Maze.</i>

15:48.021 --> 15:50.698
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:50.857 --> 15:52.358
- They took it out on the staff

15:52.442 --> 15:54.026
by attacking them
in their homes,

15:54.111 --> 15:58.280
attacking their families,
and by murdering staff.

15:58.374 --> 16:00.541
<i>In 1983, the time of the escape,</i>

16:00.701 --> 16:02.377
<i>we had 22 prison staff murdered.</i>

16:02.536 --> 16:03.703
<i>[gunshot]
[glass shatters]</i>

16:03.796 --> 16:06.872
- Prisoners were being beaten
on a daily basis.

16:06.966 --> 16:10.385
<i>There was an atmosphere
of complete distrust</i>

16:10.469 --> 16:11.803
from both sides.

16:11.887 --> 16:15.473
<i>So we were trying to shift
from that atmosphere</i>

16:15.632 --> 16:18.476
<i>into an atmosphere
which was needed to get</i>

16:18.635 --> 16:21.312
a substantial number
of prisoners out of jail.

16:21.471 --> 16:27.226
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:27.319 --> 16:28.820
<i>- The IRA prisoners</i>

16:28.979 --> 16:31.656
<i>suddenly started
being nice to the guards.</i>

16:31.740 --> 16:33.983
Start talking
about football, soccer.

16:34.067 --> 16:36.244
<i>And very, very purposely,</i>

16:36.328 --> 16:38.738
<i>prisoners started
referring to guards</i>

16:38.831 --> 16:40.999
by their first names.

16:41.083 --> 16:42.333
It was a disarming tactic.

16:42.492 --> 16:44.085
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:44.244 --> 16:46.662
<i>- With the guards more relaxed,</i>

16:46.755 --> 16:49.498
<i>tea becomes
a potential lubricant</i>

16:49.583 --> 16:52.334
<i>to get past that locked
control room door.</i>

16:52.419 --> 16:53.753
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:53.837 --> 16:57.098
- We began to make them tea
when we made our own tea.

16:57.182 --> 16:58.850
<i>- But the tea is not enough</i>

16:59.009 --> 17:01.019
<i>to have them
leave the door open.</i>

17:01.178 --> 17:03.271
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:03.355 --> 17:05.690
<i>- Now, you can pass
a cup of tea through a grill.</i>

17:05.849 --> 17:09.027
When we made toast,
you can't put a plate through.

17:09.186 --> 17:12.864
<i>- Toast could be just what's
needed to open this door.</i>

17:13.023 --> 17:14.782
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:14.941 --> 17:16.701
<i>But will the guards go for it?</i>

17:18.361 --> 17:20.038
- And we did this for weeks
and weeks and weeks

17:20.197 --> 17:21.697
<i>until we ended up,</i>

17:21.790 --> 17:23.875
<i>padlock was off, door was open.</i>

17:23.959 --> 17:26.294
<i>We could go over, set the tea
and toast in front of them,</i>

17:26.453 --> 17:27.795
<i>walk out, and close it again.</i>

17:27.880 --> 17:29.172
That became the norm.

17:30.457 --> 17:32.958
<i>- With the door open,</i>

17:33.043 --> 17:35.127
<i>the escapees still need
to figure out</i>

17:35.220 --> 17:38.714
<i>how they can subdue a guard
in the control room,</i>

17:38.807 --> 17:40.224
<i>because with a flick
of his wrist,</i>

17:40.383 --> 17:42.977
<i>he could alert the authorities
in mere seconds.</i>

17:44.471 --> 17:47.973
<i>They're going to need
something brazen and bold,</i>

17:48.067 --> 17:51.393
<i>something that would be
impossible to obtain</i>

17:51.487 --> 17:53.571
<i>within the walls of the prison.</i>

17:53.655 --> 17:56.398
- Weapons were necessary
to do it.

17:56.483 --> 18:01.829
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:01.914 --> 18:04.323
- What they needed was arms
and ammunition

18:04.407 --> 18:06.408
smuggled into the prison.

18:06.502 --> 18:08.836
<i>- To this day,
the IRA has never disclosed</i>

18:08.995 --> 18:10.421
<i>how the guns got in there.</i>

18:10.506 --> 18:13.165
It's the $64,000 question.

18:13.250 --> 18:15.835
But I think the IRA
is protecting people

18:15.928 --> 18:18.012
that helped them get the guns.

18:18.171 --> 18:21.924
<i>- What we do know is that when
the guns come into the Maze,</i>

18:22.008 --> 18:24.093
<i>they aren't delivered
to H-Block 7.</i>

18:24.177 --> 18:26.929
<i>They are smuggled into
another part of the prison</i>

18:27.022 --> 18:30.441
<i>and have to be moved
to H-Block 7.</i>

18:30.600 --> 18:33.778
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:33.937 --> 18:35.113
[gun cocks]

18:35.272 --> 18:38.357
<i>- The movement of guns
is a well-known strategy</i>

18:38.441 --> 18:40.609
<i>and tactic by the IRA.</i>

18:40.694 --> 18:43.538
They move guns quite regularly
on the outside

18:43.697 --> 18:45.614
under all sorts of scrutiny.

18:45.699 --> 18:47.116
<i>But moving it within the prison</i>

18:47.209 --> 18:49.535
<i>obviously is a lot riskier.</i>

18:49.628 --> 18:50.786
<i>- The guns come in,</i>

18:50.871 --> 18:53.956
<i>and what they were
transported in was--</i>

18:54.040 --> 18:55.383
I don't know if they know them
in America,

18:55.467 --> 18:58.127
but they're called
Dr. Marten boots.

18:58.211 --> 19:00.379
<i>- The soles of the boots
are hollowed out</i>

19:00.472 --> 19:01.547
<i>so that they can fit</i>

19:01.640 --> 19:05.476
<i>very small .22
and .25 caliber guns.</i>

19:05.635 --> 19:08.980
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:09.139 --> 19:12.817
<i>- So one person would wear
a pair of boots</i>

19:12.901 --> 19:17.405
<i>and take them on a visit
or to one of the workshops.</i>

19:17.489 --> 19:19.648
<i>And they simply swapped them</i>

19:19.733 --> 19:22.577
out of the sight
of any prison guards.

19:22.661 --> 19:26.655
<i>- But the gun transfers don't
always go exactly to plan.</i>

19:26.740 --> 19:30.826
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:30.911 --> 19:32.670
<i>On one transfer,</i>

19:32.754 --> 19:34.839
<i>a nervous prisoner
is walking back to his cell</i>

19:34.923 --> 19:36.665
<i>in H-Block 7</i>

19:36.758 --> 19:40.511
<i>wearing shiny new boots
containing the guns.</i>

19:40.670 --> 19:44.590
<i>He must remain calm, cool,
and collected.</i>

19:44.683 --> 19:49.261
<i>He needs to get to his cell
before a guard stops him.</i>

19:49.346 --> 19:51.263
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:51.356 --> 19:55.184
<i>And sure enough,
just 50 feet from his cell,</i>

19:55.268 --> 19:56.360
<i>he is stopped.</i>

19:56.519 --> 19:57.853
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:57.938 --> 19:59.614
<i>- One of the prison guards said,</i>

19:59.698 --> 20:01.616
"Did you get
a pair of new boots?"

20:01.700 --> 20:03.201
<i>- If the guard searches him</i>

20:03.360 --> 20:05.694
<i>and finds the guns in his boots,</i>

20:05.787 --> 20:08.289
<i>not only will the escape
be scrapped,</i>

20:08.448 --> 20:10.958
<i>but this now friendly H-Block</i>

20:11.117 --> 20:14.045
<i>will return to its brutal past.</i>

20:18.717 --> 20:20.209
- For several months,

20:20.293 --> 20:23.879
a group of prisoners
has been planning a mass escape

20:23.964 --> 20:27.225
from the Maze prison
in Northern Ireland.

20:27.309 --> 20:30.728
The key to the plot:
small handguns

20:30.812 --> 20:35.483
smuggled inside
in the soles of boots.

20:35.567 --> 20:37.893
Without guns,
the escapees can't hope

20:37.986 --> 20:41.313
to hold two dozen guards at bay.

20:41.406 --> 20:45.326
But now, one prisoner
is being stopped at security

20:45.410 --> 20:50.414
when a guard spots
his shiny new boots.

20:52.084 --> 20:55.920
<i>If the prisoners get searched
and the guns are found,</i>

20:56.079 --> 20:58.005
<i>the whole escape
is certainly dead</i>

20:58.090 --> 21:00.582
<i>and severe punishment
is in store</i>

21:00.667 --> 21:03.094
<i>for all the conspirators.</i>

21:03.178 --> 21:04.595
- And he said in a friendly way,

21:04.680 --> 21:07.339
his wife's name was Kith,
and he says, "That's from Kith.

21:07.424 --> 21:08.683
<i>"She sent me in these boots.</i>

21:08.767 --> 21:10.184
<i>"I'm not that fond of them,</i>

21:10.269 --> 21:11.677
but I suppose
I have to wear them."

21:11.761 --> 21:13.521
<i>And he says,
"Yeah, I like the boots,"</i>

21:13.680 --> 21:15.273
<i>you know, and went on.</i>

21:16.850 --> 21:20.019
<i>- It's a close call,
but the guns arrive</i>

21:20.112 --> 21:22.604
<i>in H-Block 7.</i>

21:22.689 --> 21:25.441
<i>The weapons are in the block.</i>

21:25.525 --> 21:29.028
<i>Now the prisoners must find
a secure place to store them.</i>

21:29.112 --> 21:33.198
<i>And the best place is
right under the guards' noses.</i>

21:33.292 --> 21:36.618
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

21:36.712 --> 21:39.038
- We found a place
in the storeroom

21:39.122 --> 21:42.383
where you store everything
for the entire block.

21:42.467 --> 21:44.885
<i>- The storeroom is
in the secure area,</i>

21:44.970 --> 21:47.713
<i>the crossbar of the H-Block.</i>

21:47.806 --> 21:50.725
- So we claim down under
the very, very bottom shelf.

21:50.809 --> 21:54.136
<i>We were able to hide them
in there, cover it over,</i>

21:54.220 --> 21:57.056
and then pack everything
back in on top of it.

21:57.140 --> 21:59.483
<i>So we were able to secure
the weapons</i>

21:59.642 --> 22:02.320
<i>until the day
before we needed them.</i>

22:02.404 --> 22:05.230
<i>- With access
to the control room</i>

22:05.315 --> 22:08.484
<i>and an arsenal of guns
stashed close by,</i>

22:08.568 --> 22:10.244
<i>the prisoners have all they need</i>

22:10.403 --> 22:12.905
<i>to get out of H-Block 7.</i>

22:12.989 --> 22:15.240
<i>But that doesn't get them
out of the Maze.</i>

22:15.334 --> 22:16.825
<i>Not even close.</i>

22:16.910 --> 22:18.744
<i>They need to secure the truck</i>

22:18.828 --> 22:20.913
<i>that can get
dozens of them to freedom.</i>

22:20.997 --> 22:24.750
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:24.843 --> 22:27.586
- So the idea came up,
we could take over the truck,

22:27.670 --> 22:29.004
<i>hijack the driver,</i>

22:29.089 --> 22:30.514
<i>and use the truck to fill it up</i>

22:30.673 --> 22:33.258
<i>with as many IRA prisoners
as possible.</i>

22:33.343 --> 22:35.844
And it was identified
as a potential weak spot

22:35.929 --> 22:38.189
because it was discovered
that this prison truck

22:38.273 --> 22:42.360
was used by prison guards
if they were moving house.

22:42.519 --> 22:44.603
<i>- So it would not
raise suspicion</i>

22:44.687 --> 22:46.781
<i>leaving the Maze's main gate.</i>

22:46.865 --> 22:49.950
<i>That is, of course, as long
as the guard driving it</i>

22:50.110 --> 22:51.777
<i>does not give them away.</i>

22:51.861 --> 22:55.122
<i>- We needed a prisoner
lying on the floor</i>

22:55.207 --> 22:57.533
to hold that prison guard,
the driver,

22:57.617 --> 23:00.127
<i>to drive the truck
out of the jail.</i>

23:00.286 --> 23:04.623
<i>I was picked as the prisoner
who would take that job.</i>

23:04.707 --> 23:06.467
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:06.551 --> 23:08.552
<i>- Even with the plan
to hijack a truck</i>

23:08.637 --> 23:11.630
<i>and hold the driver hostage,
there is still</i>

23:11.714 --> 23:14.466
<i>one more obstacle
between them and freedom.</i>

23:14.559 --> 23:17.812
<i>To leave the Maze,
you have to pass the main gate</i>

23:17.896 --> 23:21.306
<i>and then the external
British military checkpoint.</i>

23:21.391 --> 23:23.475
<i>And you can't get past
the military gate</i>

23:23.560 --> 23:26.478
<i>without a pass you receive
at the first gate.</i>

23:26.563 --> 23:30.482
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:30.567 --> 23:32.818
- The security building
was where you would get

23:32.911 --> 23:36.155
that pass that you needed
to get out of the prison

23:36.239 --> 23:37.998
<i>through the British
military checkpoint.</i>

23:38.083 --> 23:40.492
Once you get through there,
you're free, you're gone.

23:40.577 --> 23:44.496
- The security building
had to be physically taken over

23:44.581 --> 23:46.999
<i>to make sure that
under no circumstances</i>

23:47.083 --> 23:48.250
<i>was any alarms given off.</i>

23:48.334 --> 23:51.670
We had to secure that
and put our people in it

23:51.763 --> 23:53.505
while we exited

23:53.590 --> 23:55.933
<i>the main hydraulic gate
of the prison proper.</i>

23:56.017 --> 23:58.352
<i>- The catch is that
this security building</i>

23:58.511 --> 24:00.179
<i>is often full of guards,</i>

24:00.263 --> 24:03.357
<i>especially at shift changes,
since all guards</i>

24:03.442 --> 24:06.685
<i>going in and out of the prison
must check in here.</i>

24:06.778 --> 24:10.689
<i>So the prisoners must time
the escape just right</i>

24:10.773 --> 24:13.692
<i>or else they'll face
an army of guards.</i>

24:13.776 --> 24:18.947
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:19.032 --> 24:21.375
<i>Finally, they have
all the elements</i>

24:21.460 --> 24:23.627
<i>of their escape plan
figured out,</i>

24:23.712 --> 24:27.623
<i>at least in theory,
but will it work in practice?</i>

24:27.707 --> 24:30.626
<i>There's just one way
to find out.</i>

24:30.719 --> 24:32.878
<i>- We did a full dress rehearsal</i>

24:32.962 --> 24:34.296
<i>before the escape</i>

24:34.389 --> 24:35.631
to see that everything worked.

24:35.715 --> 24:38.058
Everything had to go
like clockwork.

24:38.143 --> 24:40.385
<i>There was no time
for making mistakes.</i>

24:40.479 --> 24:43.222
<i>- First, prisoners assigned
to stop guards</i>

24:43.315 --> 24:45.724
<i>from hitting alarm buttons
throughout the block</i>

24:45.808 --> 24:47.309
<i>get into position.</i>

24:47.393 --> 24:49.561
<i>Then the core escape team</i>

24:49.646 --> 24:53.157
<i>congregates in the restricted
zone on the crossbar.</i>

24:54.743 --> 24:56.485
<i>- We all went
into the storeroom.</i>

24:56.569 --> 24:57.828
<i>We didn't stay there long,</i>

24:57.987 --> 25:01.073
just gathered to make sure
that nobody said anything.

25:01.157 --> 25:03.992
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:04.077 --> 25:06.411
<i>- Will the guards notice
that something is afoot?</i>

25:06.496 --> 25:07.671
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:07.830 --> 25:11.175
<i>And will this be the end
of their escape plans?</i>

25:11.259 --> 25:13.835
- It was noticed, but...

25:13.929 --> 25:17.256
nobody paid any attention to it.

25:17.340 --> 25:18.933
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:19.017 --> 25:21.093
<i>- The dress rehearsal works.</i>

25:21.177 --> 25:23.845
<i>The full plan is now in place.</i>

25:25.273 --> 25:28.776
Take over the control room
using guns to subdue the guards

25:28.860 --> 25:31.853
and prevent any alarms
from being sounded.

25:31.947 --> 25:33.948
<i>Hijack the truck and its driver</i>

25:34.032 --> 25:37.109
<i>at H-Block 7's loading dock,</i>

25:37.202 --> 25:39.861
<i>put up to 40 prisoners
in the back of the truck,</i>

25:39.946 --> 25:41.196
<i>get through the main gate</i>

25:41.289 --> 25:44.449
<i>with the truck driver
at gunpoint,</i>

25:44.534 --> 25:47.378
<i>overwhelm security
at the military gate,</i>

25:47.537 --> 25:49.880
<i>and drive out
of the prison grounds.</i>

25:49.965 --> 25:53.050
<i>Then meet up
with their IRA contacts</i>

25:53.134 --> 25:54.802
<i>at the nearby road.</i>

25:54.886 --> 25:57.388
What can go wrong?

26:01.634 --> 26:04.303
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

26:04.396 --> 26:07.982
- September, 1983.

26:08.141 --> 26:09.900
Her Majesty's Maze prison,

26:09.985 --> 26:12.820
one of the most secure prisons
in Europe,

26:12.904 --> 26:15.230
is about to be tested.

26:15.315 --> 26:19.401
A small team of IRA prisoners
that spent five months

26:19.485 --> 26:24.164
meticulously planning
a mass escape from H-Block 7.

26:24.324 --> 26:27.835
Now they learn
from their IRA command

26:27.994 --> 26:30.412
that a date is set,

26:30.496 --> 26:33.591
Sunday, September 25th.

26:33.750 --> 26:37.169
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:37.262 --> 26:40.097
<i>The night before the escape,
Bik meets Gerry Kelly</i>

26:40.256 --> 26:44.018
<i>in the cafeteria
where a movie is playing.</i>

26:44.102 --> 26:45.594
- They turned the lights off,

26:45.687 --> 26:46.937
and they were starting
the video.

26:47.022 --> 26:48.606
<i>And the title came up
and it said,</i>

26:48.765 --> 26:51.358
<i>"I Escaped
From Devil's Island."</i>

26:51.517 --> 26:53.352
<i>That was the name of the video.</i>

26:53.445 --> 26:56.697
<i>- The film is about an escape
from an infamous prison.</i>

26:56.781 --> 26:58.023
<i>- And I went, "Oh."</i>

26:58.107 --> 27:00.451
I says, "There's a bit
of an omen for tomorrow."

27:00.610 --> 27:02.202
<i>- So the rest
of the conversation was about,</i>

27:02.287 --> 27:03.862
"Is everything okay?"

27:03.946 --> 27:05.205
<i>Everything was prepared.</i>

27:05.365 --> 27:08.292
<i>It was just a matter
of waiting for the next day.</i>

27:08.451 --> 27:12.788
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:12.872 --> 27:14.465
<i>- Sunday comes.</i>

27:14.624 --> 27:17.042
<i>Bik makes his way
to the restricted zone.</i>

27:17.126 --> 27:19.795
<i>He's tasked with making sure
the coast is clear</i>

27:19.888 --> 27:22.381
<i>and giving the signal
to start the escape.</i>

27:22.474 --> 27:23.632
<i>- My first thing that I did</i>

27:23.716 --> 27:26.060
<i>was to check
that everything was clear,</i>

27:26.144 --> 27:28.804
<i>there was no issues,
that it was calm.</i>

27:28.888 --> 27:30.389
<i>The senior officer who was there</i>

27:30.473 --> 27:32.391
<i>was supposed to leave,
but he didn't.</i>

27:32.484 --> 27:35.894
I was waiting for him
to leave the block.

27:35.978 --> 27:38.230
<i>- With the 4:00 p.m.
prison shift change</i>

27:38.323 --> 27:42.826
<i>just an hour and a half away,
Bik has a choice to make.</i>

27:42.985 --> 27:46.080
<i>Does he wait for
the senior officer to leave,</i>

27:46.239 --> 27:48.323
<i>or does he just go for it?</i>

27:48.408 --> 27:50.409
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:50.502 --> 27:51.502
- I just had to move.

27:51.661 --> 27:54.079
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:54.172 --> 27:57.666
- The escape officially began
with Bik McFarlane yelling,

27:57.750 --> 28:00.678
"Bumper," the name of the floor
polishing machines.

28:00.762 --> 28:03.004
So once "bumper" was yelled,
it was on.

28:03.098 --> 28:05.090
- So I shouted
to the prison guard down,

28:05.174 --> 28:07.351
"Is the bumper down
in A and B?"

28:07.435 --> 28:10.095
<i>And someone shouted out,
"No, it's not here.</i>

28:10.179 --> 28:12.514
<i>Try far side, C and D."</i>

28:12.607 --> 28:15.183
So that alerted everybody
on our wing, on A and B,

28:15.268 --> 28:16.685
<i>to get into position.</i>

28:16.778 --> 28:19.104
<i>So when I shouted down
for C and D,</i>

28:19.197 --> 28:20.197
<i>"Is the bumper down there?"</i>

28:20.281 --> 28:22.116
Bobby Storey shouted,
"Yes, it's here.

28:22.275 --> 28:23.275
I'll bring it out."

28:23.359 --> 28:24.785
<i>So the prison guard let him out</i>

28:24.944 --> 28:26.203
<i>through the double gates,</i>

28:26.287 --> 28:28.872
<i>and he brought the bumper
into the storeroom.</i>

28:29.031 --> 28:31.375
<i>And at the same time,
Gerry Kelly had come out</i>

28:31.534 --> 28:34.202
with something to be brought
and was allowed out.

28:34.287 --> 28:36.288
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:36.372 --> 28:40.134
<i>- The core escape team
congregates in the storeroom.</i>

28:40.293 --> 28:41.885
<i>Each man grabs his weapon.</i>

28:42.044 --> 28:46.473
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:46.632 --> 28:48.058
- We were all in place to move.

28:48.217 --> 28:49.718
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:49.811 --> 28:51.887
<i>- Bobby Storey
and another prisoner</i>

28:51.971 --> 28:53.555
<i>entered the officer's lunchroom</i>

28:53.639 --> 28:55.223
<i>in the restricted zone</i>

28:55.316 --> 28:57.392
<i>where there are
four prison guards.</i>

28:57.485 --> 28:59.478
- Bobby Storey
produced his weapon.

28:59.571 --> 29:02.230
He cocked it for effect.

29:02.315 --> 29:04.575
<i>And he said--
And he said it quietly,</i>

29:04.734 --> 29:06.326
"Get on the ground."

29:06.411 --> 29:08.162
<i>And they looked up
and laughed at him.</i>

29:08.321 --> 29:09.571
Thought it was a joke
in the middle

29:09.664 --> 29:11.081
of the most secure prison
in Europe.

29:11.240 --> 29:12.741
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:12.825 --> 29:14.585
<i>"It's not a joke.
Get on the ground.</i>

29:14.669 --> 29:16.253
<i>"Do exactly what I say
and you'll be okay.</i>

29:16.337 --> 29:19.498
If youse don't,
we've got guns."

29:19.582 --> 29:21.008
<i>- Once they had the guns,</i>

29:21.167 --> 29:23.251
<i>they had the power
and the control.</i>

29:23.336 --> 29:25.754
The prisoners didn't have
to prove they're bona fide.

29:25.847 --> 29:29.516
Staff knew that
if the prisoners were intent,

29:29.675 --> 29:31.351
<i>that they were
in serious danger.</i>

29:31.511 --> 29:34.271
<i>So they were going to comply.</i>

29:34.355 --> 29:36.523
- So what happened, it's almost
like a ripple effect.

29:36.608 --> 29:39.017
If you drop a pebble
into a pool of water,

29:39.101 --> 29:40.936
<i>the ripples all go out
simultaneously,</i>

29:41.020 --> 29:42.196
<i>concentrically.</i>

29:42.280 --> 29:45.524
<i>- Then people who were
down in the blocks,</i>

29:45.608 --> 29:47.367
<i>they knew that it was
their time then</i>

29:47.527 --> 29:49.369
<i>to pull them away from the alarm</i>

29:49.529 --> 29:50.537
so you can't get out the alarm.

29:50.696 --> 29:52.697
<i>- I would say 20 seconds,</i>

29:52.791 --> 29:56.126
everybody was under arrest
in any vulnerable positions.

29:56.285 --> 29:57.702
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:57.787 --> 29:59.704
<i>- Gerry Kelly's next job</i>

29:59.789 --> 30:01.623
<i>is to take over the control room</i>

30:01.707 --> 30:03.542
<i>in the restricted zone.</i>

30:03.626 --> 30:05.210
<i>This is one of the most
critical moments</i>

30:05.303 --> 30:07.471
<i>in the escape plan.</i>

30:07.630 --> 30:10.808
<i>If he fails, they will
all be caught for sure.</i>

30:10.967 --> 30:13.727
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:13.812 --> 30:16.146
- I point the weapon
in through the grill.

30:16.305 --> 30:17.806
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:17.899 --> 30:20.058
<i>I knew the prison guard
that was on.</i>

30:20.142 --> 30:22.811
<i>And I said, "John,
this is an IRA operation.</i>

30:22.895 --> 30:24.312
"This is a gun.

30:24.405 --> 30:25.981
I need you to do exactly
what I tell you."

30:26.074 --> 30:27.732
- They didn't want
to hurt anybody.

30:27.826 --> 30:29.743
But they would not hesitate
to hurt somebody

30:29.902 --> 30:32.153
if they try to raise the alarm.

30:32.238 --> 30:34.990
<i>- Gerry tells the guard
to get down on the ground</i>

30:35.074 --> 30:37.993
<i>so that he won't be able
to hit the alarm buttons.</i>

30:38.086 --> 30:40.912
- I could see him
just sizing it up.

30:41.005 --> 30:43.173
<i>- If the guard is going
to raise the alarm,</i>

30:43.332 --> 30:46.418
<i>it has to be now.</i>

30:46.502 --> 30:48.003
- And I says, "John, don't."

30:48.087 --> 30:51.765
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:51.850 --> 30:53.341
And he got down on the ground.

30:53.426 --> 30:55.352
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:55.511 --> 30:58.522
<i>- But just as John Adams
lies down on the ground,</i>

30:58.681 --> 31:01.191
<i>an unaccounted for guard
comes out of the toilet</i>

31:01.276 --> 31:03.944
<i>into the main lobby
of the restricted zone.</i>

31:04.028 --> 31:07.522
[toilet flushes]

31:07.607 --> 31:10.358
- Gerry Kelly looked away
momentarily.

31:10.443 --> 31:13.120
<i>And Mr. Adams
took his opportunity,</i>

31:13.279 --> 31:14.872
despite the risk to himself,

31:14.956 --> 31:18.125
did try to close the door
to secure the control room

31:18.284 --> 31:19.877
so that he could
raise the alarm.

31:20.036 --> 31:21.786
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:21.880 --> 31:23.705
- I can't see what's happening.
And I hear two shots.

31:23.798 --> 31:26.049
[gunshots]

31:31.380 --> 31:34.633
- It's about 2:50
in the afternoon on Sunday,

31:34.717 --> 31:38.645
September 25, 1983.

31:38.730 --> 31:41.222
Less than 20 minutes
into the escape

31:41.307 --> 31:43.975
from Her Majesty's Maze prison,

31:44.060 --> 31:47.738
things are already
getting out of control.

31:47.822 --> 31:49.740
IRA prisoner Gerry Kelly

31:49.899 --> 31:52.409
has secured the nerve center
of H-Block 7.

31:53.912 --> 31:57.822
But in the process,
a guard has been shot.

31:57.916 --> 32:01.335
- According to the official
report into the escape,

32:01.419 --> 32:05.163
it was Gerry Kelly who shot
a prison officer in the head,

32:05.256 --> 32:06.915
<i>John Adams.</i>

32:06.999 --> 32:08.750
[gunshots]

32:08.834 --> 32:10.260
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

32:10.419 --> 32:12.596
<i>He was attempting
to raise the alarm.</i>

32:12.680 --> 32:16.174
- When he came to,
I went over to him.

32:16.258 --> 32:18.760
And I said, "Are you okay?"

32:18.844 --> 32:21.596
<i>I just wanted to know
if he could talk.</i>

32:21.681 --> 32:24.691
And I says, "What did you
do that for, John?"

32:24.776 --> 32:26.944
And he says, "I know, I know."

32:27.028 --> 32:29.696
<i>And I says, "Well, we're
getting you medical attention</i>

32:29.781 --> 32:31.949
<i>as soon as we possibly can."</i>

32:32.033 --> 32:34.109
<i>- The officer isn't
the only guard injured</i>

32:34.193 --> 32:35.869
<i>during the taking of the block.</i>

32:35.954 --> 32:38.029
<i>Several others are wounded.</i>

32:38.114 --> 32:40.540
<i>The guards now know
that the prisoners</i>

32:40.625 --> 32:42.709
<i>are deadly serious.</i>

32:42.794 --> 32:45.286
- All guards who were arrested

32:45.371 --> 32:49.049
were brought to a classroom.

32:49.133 --> 32:53.136
<i>Took the uniforms
from whichever ones we needed.</i>

32:53.295 --> 32:55.389
<i>And we gave them, like, a poncho</i>

32:55.473 --> 32:58.633
and we put pillowcase hoods
over their heads

32:58.718 --> 33:00.811
<i>so they couldn't see
who was guarding them,</i>

33:00.970 --> 33:03.138
<i>who was staying behind
to guard them.</i>

33:03.222 --> 33:05.732
<i>- The escapees now have
complete control</i>

33:05.891 --> 33:07.392
<i>over the H-Block guards.</i>

33:07.476 --> 33:13.573
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:13.658 --> 33:16.818
<i>The team moves into
the second part of their plan:</i>

33:16.902 --> 33:19.320
<i>wait for the food truck
to arrive.</i>

33:19.405 --> 33:22.574
<i>It's scheduled to get
to H-Block 7 at 3:15.</i>

33:22.667 --> 33:25.252
<i>Timing is critical.</i>

33:25.411 --> 33:27.912
<i>The chance of their takeover
being discovered increases</i>

33:27.997 --> 33:30.007
<i>every second that ticks by.</i>

33:30.091 --> 33:31.925
<i>If they are late
even by one minute,</i>

33:32.084 --> 33:33.668
<i>they run the risk</i>

33:33.753 --> 33:35.846
<i>of the prison
shift change occurring,</i>

33:35.930 --> 33:39.257
<i>which will mean more guards
at the prison's main gate.</i>

33:39.341 --> 33:41.101
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:41.260 --> 33:42.927
<i>And the truck is late.</i>

33:43.012 --> 33:49.860
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:51.771 --> 33:54.022
- The food truck came late.

33:54.106 --> 33:55.282
<i>And this was the part
of the escape</i>

33:55.366 --> 33:56.775
<i>that you couldn't rehearse.</i>

33:56.859 --> 33:58.368
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:58.453 --> 34:00.278
<i>- The driver is greeted
at gunpoint.</i>

34:00.362 --> 34:02.122
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:02.281 --> 34:04.291
<i>The message is clear.</i>

34:04.450 --> 34:07.452
<i>Do what we say, or else.</i>

34:07.545 --> 34:09.871
- So what happened then was,
they brought the driver,

34:09.955 --> 34:12.215
<i>and we had
taken over the medics room</i>

34:12.300 --> 34:14.209
<i>and displayed a large board
with the maps</i>

34:14.293 --> 34:16.211
<i>and the diagrams of the camp.</i>

34:16.295 --> 34:19.056
<i>We put pistols and ammunition
on the table.</i>

34:19.140 --> 34:21.641
<i>- And he's told he's now part
of the escape plan.</i>

34:21.801 --> 34:24.886
<i>He is tied to a piece of cord</i>

34:24.979 --> 34:27.064
<i>that is linked
to the hand grenade.</i>

34:27.148 --> 34:28.723
<i>So alongside that,</i>

34:28.808 --> 34:31.059
<i>Gerry Kelly,
he's donned a prison uniform,</i>

34:31.143 --> 34:34.488
he's lying there with his gun
trained on the driver.

34:34.647 --> 34:35.730
- There was no grenade,

34:35.823 --> 34:38.325
but at this stage,
he was believing

34:38.409 --> 34:40.994
sort of anything
that we were telling him.

34:41.079 --> 34:43.822
<i>- Now that they were
in control of the food truck,</i>

34:43.906 --> 34:46.416
<i>37 prisoners pile into back.</i>

34:46.575 --> 34:48.335
And that is now
this escape vehicle

34:48.419 --> 34:49.753
that they hope will drive them

34:49.837 --> 34:54.091
out of the Maze complex
into freedom.

34:54.250 --> 34:59.429
<i>- That is, if it can get
to the main gate</i>

34:59.514 --> 35:02.340
<i>before the 4:00 p.m.
shift change.</i>

35:02.424 --> 35:04.351
<i>The stakes are getting higher
every minute.</i>

35:04.510 --> 35:07.095
<i>The driver, held at gunpoint,</i>

35:07.179 --> 35:09.848
<i>tries to stay calm
as he starts the engine</i>

35:09.941 --> 35:11.015
<i>and pulls out.</i>

35:11.100 --> 35:13.026
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:13.185 --> 35:15.353
<i>There is no going back.</i>

35:15.437 --> 35:19.032
<i>- Well, my nerves were
not exactly very calm</i>

35:19.191 --> 35:20.358
in the back of the truck.

35:20.451 --> 35:23.036
I was standing up
as Bobby Storey was standing.

35:23.121 --> 35:26.364
Everybody else was seated.
Complete silence.

35:26.448 --> 35:28.625
We told everybody
when we got in,

35:28.784 --> 35:31.795
"Nobody speak a word
until we're outside."

35:31.879 --> 35:34.706
<i>Total silence.
The adrenaline was pumping.</i>

35:34.790 --> 35:36.207
<i>- The food truck
makes it through</i>

35:36.292 --> 35:38.385
<i>several low-level
security checkpoints</i>

35:38.544 --> 35:40.211
<i>without much fanfare.</i>

35:40.296 --> 35:46.301
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:46.385 --> 35:48.979
<i>Finally, the truck reaches
the security building</i>

35:49.063 --> 35:50.555
<i>near the main gate</i>

35:50.639 --> 35:53.725
<i>with only ten minutes
to shift change.</i>

35:53.818 --> 35:58.905
<i>Here, nine prisoners disguised
in guard uniforms</i>

35:59.064 --> 36:00.907
<i>get out of the truck.</i>

36:01.066 --> 36:04.068
<i>They force the security guards
in the building at gunpoint</i>

36:04.153 --> 36:08.323
<i>to give them the official pass
needed at the next gate,</i>

36:08.407 --> 36:10.241
<i>the British military gate.</i>

36:10.326 --> 36:14.421
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:14.505 --> 36:16.590
<i>But as they are taking over
the security building,</i>

36:16.749 --> 36:18.341
<i>it's getting closer and closer</i>

36:18.426 --> 36:21.011
<i>to the shift change
at the prison.</i>

36:21.170 --> 36:26.007
- We were at least
20 minutes late or later

36:26.091 --> 36:28.518
than we should have been
arriving at this area.

36:28.603 --> 36:33.106
There should only have been
maximum six guards

36:33.265 --> 36:35.266
<i>in control of this area.</i>

36:35.351 --> 36:38.528
<i>But because it was
20 minutes or more late,</i>

36:38.687 --> 36:40.864
<i>so many guards
started coming on duty</i>

36:40.948 --> 36:43.033
and so many started
coming off duty.

36:43.192 --> 36:46.277
So numbers began to build up
and build up.

36:46.362 --> 36:49.614
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:49.698 --> 36:52.450
<i>- The only option
for the nine fake guards</i>

36:52.534 --> 36:54.794
<i>is to keep taking hostages.</i>

36:54.879 --> 36:56.371
<i>But there are only
so many guards</i>

36:56.455 --> 36:58.298
<i>the prisoners can control.</i>

36:58.382 --> 37:00.291
<i>Time is running out.</i>

37:00.376 --> 37:01.718
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:01.802 --> 37:05.055
<i>They've got to do something,
or else it's all over.</i>

37:11.229 --> 37:14.138
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

37:14.223 --> 37:16.057
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:16.141 --> 37:18.401
- It's just after 4:00 p.m.

37:18.486 --> 37:21.062
The most secure prison
in Western Europe

37:21.155 --> 37:24.983
is under attack from the inside.

37:25.076 --> 37:29.487
38 IRA prisoners have succeeded
in breaking free

37:29.580 --> 37:33.074
of the unbreakable H-Block
where they are imprisoned.

37:33.158 --> 37:35.493
<i>But they're late
to the main gate.</i>

37:35.586 --> 37:39.839
Now they are desperate
to control almost 40 officers

37:39.924 --> 37:42.417
they're holding
in a security building

37:42.501 --> 37:44.085
next to the gate.

37:44.169 --> 37:46.680
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:46.764 --> 37:51.426
- Between 35 and 40 prison
guards lying down on the floor.

37:51.510 --> 37:54.929
<i>So they're starting to pile up
in the security building.</i>

37:55.014 --> 37:56.940
<i>- The situation
in the security building</i>

37:57.024 --> 37:59.183
<i>is quickly spiraling
out of control.</i>

37:59.268 --> 38:01.269
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:01.353 --> 38:03.613
- A guard coming off duty,

38:03.698 --> 38:06.024
he looked in and he could see
there was something wrong,

38:06.108 --> 38:07.200
<i>and he ran</i>

38:07.285 --> 38:09.035
<i>blowing the security whistle,
the alarm.</i>

38:09.120 --> 38:10.787
So I ran over to Bobby
and I said,

38:10.871 --> 38:12.280
"Bobby, that's the alarm."

38:12.373 --> 38:14.365
<i>Bobby said to me, "Open
the front gate of the jail."</i>

38:14.450 --> 38:15.867
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:15.951 --> 38:18.128
And there's a big hydraulic
lever on the hydraulic gate.

38:18.212 --> 38:19.620
And as I opened that gate,

38:19.705 --> 38:21.214
<i>there were about
ten prison guards</i>

38:21.373 --> 38:22.716
<i>waiting to get on duty.</i>

38:22.800 --> 38:25.126
And one of them recognized me.

38:25.210 --> 38:26.461
And then I just produced
a pistol

38:26.545 --> 38:27.887
and told him to stay back.

38:27.972 --> 38:29.547
<i>- Bik is able to open the gate,</i>

38:29.631 --> 38:31.641
<i>but several guards
waiting on the other side</i>

38:31.800 --> 38:33.977
<i>drive two cars
in front of the gate,</i>

38:34.061 --> 38:36.554
<i>effectively blocking the truck.</i>

38:36.638 --> 38:37.972
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:38.057 --> 38:39.816
<i>- At this point,</i>

38:39.975 --> 38:41.985
the original plan
of using the food truck

38:42.069 --> 38:45.563
to drive the prisoners
out of the Maze complex

38:45.647 --> 38:47.065
<i>to freedom has collapsed.</i>

38:47.149 --> 38:48.566
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:48.650 --> 38:50.485
<i>- Time is running out.</i>

38:50.569 --> 38:52.820
<i>Bik turns to Bobby for guidance.</i>

38:52.905 --> 38:54.831
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:54.915 --> 38:56.499
- They said
they've drove cars in.

38:56.584 --> 38:59.077
And he said to me, "Open
the back gate of the truck."

38:59.161 --> 39:00.661
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:00.746 --> 39:04.090
<i>- It's time for plan B,
or maybe plan C:</i>

39:04.175 --> 39:06.676
<i>run.</i>

39:06.835 --> 39:09.179
<i>- All of our guys
in civilian clothes</i>

39:09.338 --> 39:11.255
<i>jumped out of the back
of the truck...</i>

39:11.340 --> 39:12.924
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:13.017 --> 39:14.851
- [groans]

39:15.010 --> 39:18.429
<i>- Which meant we now had
38 people.</i>

39:18.522 --> 39:21.516
The prison guards had a number
of people coming on,

39:21.609 --> 39:24.602
30 to 40 inside,
so you had a melee

39:24.686 --> 39:28.439
<i>of anywhere up to about 80
or 90 people,</i>

39:28.532 --> 39:31.776
prison guards, IRA prisoners,
fighting in that area.

39:31.860 --> 39:33.778
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:33.871 --> 39:36.289
<i>- At this point,
it descends into a brawl.</i>

39:36.374 --> 39:38.699
And so there are prisoners
trying to get out of there.

39:38.784 --> 39:41.452
There are guards
trying to detain them.

39:41.537 --> 39:43.121
<i>All hell broke loose.</i>

39:43.205 --> 39:45.632
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:45.716 --> 39:46.633
<i>- So at this stage,</i>

39:46.717 --> 39:48.960
the prisoners knew
the game was up.

39:49.044 --> 39:51.379
So it was every man for himself.

39:51.472 --> 39:53.056
- So we made a run for the gate,

39:53.140 --> 39:54.799
fought our way out to the front.

39:54.883 --> 39:57.635
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:57.728 --> 40:00.230
<i>- So the 19 that really got
beyond the perimeter</i>

40:00.314 --> 40:01.731
and got away,

40:01.890 --> 40:03.474
they had to go over
a barbed wire fence.

40:03.559 --> 40:06.811
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:06.904 --> 40:08.905
<i>- It was actually
a British Ministry of Defence</i>

40:08.989 --> 40:11.649
<i>outer fence, and I knew
it could cut you up.</i>

40:11.733 --> 40:14.411
And I just run and jumped
as far onto the wire

40:14.495 --> 40:15.653
as I possibly could.

40:15.737 --> 40:22.660
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:22.753 --> 40:24.829
And I fell flat.

40:24.922 --> 40:27.081
<i>When I was about to get up,
I can only describe it as,</i>

40:27.174 --> 40:29.509
if you watch a war film,
you know,

40:29.593 --> 40:31.428
<i>and a troops are going over,</i>

40:31.587 --> 40:34.088
there's a guy
who falls as a bridge

40:34.173 --> 40:36.090
<i>so his people can
get across it faster.</i>

40:36.175 --> 40:38.843
<i>- While Gerry is stuck,
gunfire rings out.</i>

40:38.927 --> 40:42.430
[gunfire]

40:42.514 --> 40:45.433
<i>A prisoner and a guard
are shot in the chaos.</i>

40:45.526 --> 40:47.360
<i>And now Gerry is a sitting duck</i>

40:47.445 --> 40:49.437
<i>trapped in the barbed wire.</i>

40:49.521 --> 40:51.614
- All I was thinking was,
"Lads, lads, come on.

40:51.699 --> 40:52.857
<i>Pick me up."</i>

40:52.941 --> 40:55.526
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:55.611 --> 40:58.872
<i>- Eventually, a fellow escapee
risks his life</i>

40:58.956 --> 41:00.531
<i>to save Gerry's.</i>

41:00.624 --> 41:01.875
<i>- And I get out.</i>

41:01.959 --> 41:03.951
<i>I had blood on my face
from the barbed wire.</i>

41:04.036 --> 41:08.047
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:08.132 --> 41:09.707
<i>- After clearing
the military fence,</i>

41:09.800 --> 41:12.469
<i>the escapees split up
further into groups.</i>

41:12.553 --> 41:15.463
<i>Some travel towards
surrounding farmhouses.</i>

41:15.547 --> 41:17.390
<i>Some commandeer vehicles.</i>

41:17.475 --> 41:19.309
- It didn't take long, you know,

41:19.468 --> 41:21.219
for the authorities
to set up checkpoints,

41:21.303 --> 41:26.149
and news of the escape
spread fairly quickly.

41:26.233 --> 41:28.651
<i>- Roadblocks and foot patrols
are quickly established</i>

41:28.810 --> 41:31.062
<i>to search
for the escaped prisoners.</i>

41:31.146 --> 41:33.573
<i>Helicopters circle
the surrounding area.</i>

41:33.657 --> 41:35.816
<i>A few prisoners are arrested</i>

41:35.901 --> 41:38.328
<i>right near the perimeter
of the prison.</i>

41:38.412 --> 41:41.405
<i>But many do make it
all the way to freedom.</i>

41:41.490 --> 41:44.083
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:44.243 --> 41:46.836
<i>- Well, Bik and Gerry both
made their ways down south</i>

41:46.995 --> 41:49.247
and would have reported back
to the IRA for duty.

41:49.331 --> 41:52.509
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:52.593 --> 41:55.920
They eventually got over
to Europe, mainland Europe.

41:56.013 --> 41:57.922
<i>- But the long reach
of the British government</i>

41:58.006 --> 42:00.683
<i>eventually nabs both Gerry Kelly</i>

42:00.842 --> 42:04.095
<i>and Bik McFarlane in Amsterdam.</i>

42:04.179 --> 42:06.681
<i>They are sent back
to the same H-Block</i>

42:06.765 --> 42:10.101
<i>they had worked so hard
to get free of.</i>

42:10.185 --> 42:14.939
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:15.023 --> 42:18.451
The Maze breakout cost the life
of one guard

42:18.610 --> 42:20.444
and injured 20 more.

42:20.529 --> 42:22.196
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:22.281 --> 42:26.209
It was a violent
and traumatic escape.

42:27.703 --> 42:30.204
Bik McFarlane was released
from the Maze

42:30.289 --> 42:32.715
for the last time in 1997.

42:34.293 --> 42:38.388
<i>Gerry Kelly got out in 1989
and became a politician.</i>

42:38.472 --> 42:40.715
<i>He helped negotiate
the end of the Troubles</i>

42:40.799 --> 42:44.552
with the 1998
Good Friday Agreement.

42:44.645 --> 42:46.804
Part of the agreement
was the release

42:46.888 --> 42:48.806
of many prisoners at the Maze.

42:48.890 --> 42:52.735
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:52.894 --> 42:56.731
<i>In 2000, the notorious prison
was closed</i>

42:56.815 --> 42:58.658
<i>and partially demolished.</i>

42:58.742 --> 43:01.744
Only one of the H-Blocks
was kept intact

43:01.829 --> 43:03.654
in the hope that, one day,

43:03.739 --> 43:08.251
it might be transformed
into a museum of peace.
